# Knowledge graph — [APP_NAME]

This folder is the **tacit institutional knowledge** of [APP_NAME] —
the things a senior engineer who has been here for years knows, that a
new contributor (human or AI) cannot derive from reading the code alone.

It is **the** ingredient that makes Claude (via rsct-mcp) propose
solutions a senior architect would propose, instead of generic ones.
Without these files populated, the framework still works mechanically
but cannot deliver the "AI participated in the company's evolution"
experience.

---

## What lives here

Ten files, each a different facet of the tacit knowledge. All
append-only, all read by `rsct_get_knowledge(category=<name>)`.

| File | What it captures | Read most when |
|---|---|---|
| [business-glossary.md](./business-glossary.md) | Domain vocabulary — terms and their canonical meaning here | Planning, code review, naming things |
| [business-rules.md](./business-rules.md) | Invariants of the domain — non-negotiable rules | Spec phase, schema/migration design |
| [anti-decisions.md](./anti-decisions.md) | Graveyard — what was tried and abandoned, with why | Research phase, before proposing options |
| [incident-log.md](./incident-log.md) | Outages and near-misses + prevention reflexes | Any task touching incident-prone areas |
| [stakeholder-map.md](./stakeholder-map.md) | Who approves what, how to reach them | Before any change that needs sign-off |
| [team-capabilities.md](./team-capabilities.md) | What the team can build and maintain | Spec phase — proposing achievable options |
| [vendor-relationships.md](./vendor-relationships.md) | Third parties, why chosen, churn cost | Research — propose what we already pay for |
| [cost-constraints.md](./cost-constraints.md) | Where money bleeds, design reflexes around cost | Spec — weigh operational cost |
| [workflow-rituals.md](./workflow-rituals.md) | How PRs/deploys/incidents actually flow | Anything that ships or escalates |
| [domain-edge-cases.md](./domain-edge-cases.md) | The weird scenarios the domain loves | Spec + test strategy |

Plus, at the project root (not in this folder):
- [`documentation/decisions.md`](../decisions.md) — formal ADRs and firm premises (existed before the knowledge graph; complementary).
- [`documentation/architecture.md`](../architecture.md) — current architecture, modules, impact maps.
- [`documentation/infrastructure.md`](../infrastructure.md) — current runtime infrastructure inventory.

