## MCP integration (how the graph is consumed)

Claude (via rsct-mcp) reads this folder through:

- `rsct_get_knowledge(category)` — returns the requested file, optionally
filtered by a query string.
- `rsct_check_premise(claim, against)` — heuristically matches a planning
claim against `business-rules.md` + `decisions.md` + `anti-decisions.md`.
- Phase brief auto-loading — `rsct_phase_research_start` and
`rsct_phase_spec_start` automatically pull relevant categories based on
the task's classification.
- Persona reviews — each persona has a `knowledge_categories[]` list
declaring which graph files it consults during review.

Capture tools (called by phase tools when triggers fire):

- `rsct_capture_anti_decision`, `rsct_capture_incident`,
`rsct_capture_vendor_choice`, `rsct_capture_glossary_term`,
`rsct_capture_business_rule`, `rsct_capture_workflow`,
`rsct_capture_override` — each appends a well-formed entry to the
appropriate file. See `mcp-server/README.md` for the full list and
JSON schemas.

